eration of the products used for calibration, and discuss the efficacy\nof the corrections. The relative uncertainties on the bias and flatfield frames\nare low, of the order of 0.2 and 0.1 percents, respectively. The uncertainty on\nthe absolute radiometric calibration is of 3 percents, which is quite low for\nsuch an instrument. The straylight adds an estimated about 1 percent error to\nthe absolute calibration. The residuals after corrections of the straylight and\nbias offsets are of the order of a few DNs to tens of DNs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 9 Oct 2022 18:47:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
